<task id="AIPU2-100" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Cross-pane: Citation click in Workspace highlights source in Context</title>
    <phase>5</phase>
    <tags>frontend, integration, cross-pane</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-074, AIPU2-080, AIPU2-081</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    Wire up the cross-pane citation highlight flow so that when a user clicks a citation link
    inside a WorkspaceWidget, the Context pane scrolls to and highlights the source passage
    in the relevant source widget. This is a key discoverability feature: users should be
    able to trace AI-generated citations back to the underlying document or search result
    without manually navigating. Uses PaneEventBus (AIPU2-074) as the event backbone,
    CitationWidget (AIPU2-080) as the source consumer, and SearchResultsWidget (AIPU2-081)
    as a secondary path.
  </prompt>
  <role>Frontend developer with experience in React event-driven architectures and PCF/Code Page integration patterns.</role>
  <goal>
    Clicking any citation link inside a WorkspaceWidget dispatches a CrossPaneLinkEvent via
    PaneEventBus. The ContextPaneController receives the event, identifies the correct source
    widget (CitationWidget or SearchResultsWidget), scrolls to the referenced passage, and
    applies a transient highlight animation. The full flow works in both the SearchResultsWidget
    and CitationWidget paths.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r2/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/theme-consistency.md</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/WorkspacePane</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/ContextPane</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Review PaneEventBus API (AIPU2-074 output) and confirm CrossPaneLinkEvent shape: { type: 'cross-pane-link', sourceWidgetId: string, citationId: string, targetWidgetType: 'citation' | 'search-results', anchorRef: string }.</step>
    <step>In WorkspaceWidget base class, add an onLink callback prop. When a citation anchor is clicked, call onLink with the citation metadata; WorkspaceWidget wrapper dispatches CrossPaneLinkEvent via PaneEventBus.</step>
    <step>In ContextPaneController, subscribe to CrossPaneLinkEvent on mount and unsubscribe on unmount. On receipt, identify the active context widget by targetWidgetType.</step>
    <step>Implement scrollToAndHighlight(anchorRef) in CitationWidget: scroll the citation entry into view, apply a 1.5s Fluent token-based highlight animation (backgroundColorBrandBackground2 fading to transparent), then clear.</step>
    <step>Implement the same scrollToAndHighlight in SearchResultsWidget for the search-results path.</step>
    <step>Wire up the SearchResultsWidget -> CitationWidget flow: if the active context widget is SearchResultsWidget and the citation maps to a search result, highlight the result row.</step>
    <step>Write a manual integration test: load a document in WorkspaceWidget, trigger AI response with citations, click citation, verify Context pane highlights the correct source. Cover both widget paths.</step>
    <step>Verify highlight uses only Fluent UI v9 tokens — no hard-coded colors (ADR-021).</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Clicking a citation link in any WorkspaceWidget dispatches CrossPaneLinkEvent via PaneEventBus within 50ms of the click.</criterion>
    <criterion>ContextPaneController receives the event and calls scrollToAndHighlight on the correct widget.</criterion>
    <criterion>The target widget scrolls the cited passage into view and applies a visible highlight animation.</criterion>
    <criterion>Highlight animation uses Fluent UI v9 tokens exclusively — no hard-coded colors.</criterion>
    <criterion>The flow works for both the CitationWidget path and the SearchResultsWidget path.</criterion>
    <criterion>No memory leaks: PaneEventBus subscription is cleaned up on ContextPaneController unmount.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
